The paper deals with multi-person pose estimation using convolutional neural networks and Markov random fields, which are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses an algorithm that combines efficiency with provable bounds, which suggests that it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses the MPII-Multiperson dataset, which is commonly used in multimedia analysis and retrieval, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the use of Bender's decomposition, which is a technique commonly used in robotics and control, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.RO (Robotics).
